Le #MEV consiste à exploiter les données des transactions dans le #mempool et d'en intercaler une nouvelle à un moment bien précis.

C'est donc un processus de lecture et d'écriture dont certains tirent parti pour mener des attaques, comme l'attaque Sandwich ! https://t.co/KrTycnjSkO

🔸 Miner Extractable Value (PoW) https://t.co/mO7J26kzq8

Ce que l’on appelle couramment l’attaque sandwich en #crypto est en réalité une manipulation de marché en deux étapes.

La première consiste à modifier l’ordre des transactions dans un bloc (via le #MEV) et la seconde, à manipuler le marché afin d’obtenir des profits. https://t.co/Iub6zSYEYQ

What the heck is #MEV (miner extractable value)? let's explain a simple example of it using something familiar: Shrek

When we boil it down, the main plot of Shrek is analogous to a simple smart contract transaction being exploited by self-interested miners/sequencers/validators.

The counter to this is that profit maximalism is attractive. This is true - and people who employ gETH and Erigon #MEV will take market share.

But we can agree to close the extractive gap in order to prevent this asymmetry.
Because of this, arguments not to mitigate #MEV are asocial in an otherwise socially determinate system.
Sure, this means that #MEV could simply be displaced, but displacement means that it is not a component of core infrastructure.

What I find really interesting about many peoples' argument around #MEV is that they concede it is extractive.

An extractive action sacrifices the liberty of the space. We can be intentional about removing it.

The thing about #MEV is that it's treated as though it's unavoidable. It's not. 

We can agree to avoid if we work toward solving it, but that takes a collective effort.
